<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25079e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25079e">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25079e"> 79(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">G</font> exchange name</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mr. Herbert Spencer remarks, that &lsquo;by absorbing each other&apos;s blood, men are supposed to establish actual community of nature&rsquo;; and as it is a widely diffused belief that the name is vitally connected with its owner, &lsquo;to exchange names is to establish some participating in one another&apos;s being.&rsquo; Hence the blending is regarded as more complete when <mark>exchange of name</mark> goes with the mingling of blood, making even more obligatory the rendering of services between those who are no longer aliens to each other. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 144</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14047n" href="c14all.htm#c14047n">VI.C.14:047(n)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
